description:
The University of Messina (UniME) is located in Sicily, in the city of Messina. It was founded in 1548 an it is one of the oldest universities in Italy. UniME enjoys a long tradition as a driving force in the Mediterranean area and is strongly committed to growth as evident in its policy of internationalization and expansion.  It has a strong international component, with agreements from all over the world.  Exchange program mes, double degree and joint-degree program mes are all part of the international opportunities available to students. Because of the European Credit Transfer System, students may earn credits and take exams while they are studying abroad.  The University has 12 Departments, 94 degree program mes including 12  taught in English.  There are 15 Ph. D. Program mes, 21 Vocational 1-year Master degrees.

UniME currently has a student population of more than 15,000 students, coming from 70 different countries. There are 1100 professors, including 16 from foreign countries.

The degree program mes taught in English are as follows:

1) Six-year single cycle degree programme in Medicine and Surgery;

2) Bachelor's degree in Civil engineering

3) Bachelor's degree in data analysis

4) Bachelor's degree in Political Sciences and International Relations

5) Master's Degree in Cognitive science and theory of communication;

6) Master's Degree in Engineering and Computer Science;

7)  Master's Degree in Condensed Matter Physics;

8) Master's Degree in Geophysical Sciences and Seismic Risk;

9) Master's Degree in Data Science

10) Vocational Master in Banking and Finance.

11) Vocational Master in Food, Quality and International Management

12) Vocational Master in Airline management and regulation of the aviation industry

All degree program mes are taught by highly qualified professors with extensive international experience, they are job-oriented and students the possibility to carry out a trainee ship in Italy or abroad.
